The Tanzania Zambia Railway Authority 
is seeking $770 million to improve operations on the line it
runs between the two countries, Managing Director Akashambatwa
Mbikusita-Lewanika said.  The two countries are expected to contribute equally to the
budget, Mbikusita-Lewanika said today in an e-mailed statement
from its headquarters in Dar es Salaam, Tanzaniaâ€™s commercial
